cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.ST

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper deals with the conversion of continuous-time stochastic processes to discrete-time signals, which is a fundamental problem in signal processing. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the degree of sparsity of stochastic processes, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents numerical examples of sparse signals generated from the continuous-domain model, which falls under the scope of numerical analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The concept of sparsity is also relevant in machine learning, where it is used to reduce the complexity of models and improve their interpretability. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper deals with the characterization of stochastic processes and their correlation properties, which is a topic of interest in statistics.
